						SUPPORT VECTOR MACHINE (SVM)

Support Vector Machine (SVM) is a supervised machine learning algorithm used for both classification and regression tasks. It is mainly used for classification problems by finding the optimal hyperplane that best separates different classes in a dataset. The algorithm selects the hyperplane that maximizes the distance (margin) between the nearest data points of different classes, known as support vectors. SVM is highly effective for high-dimensional datasets and is widely used in image recognition, text classification, and medical diagnosis.

